  "body": "disclaimer: this is not from a stock geth version. It has a commit of @chriseth on top to dump contract addresses with creation code. (https://github.com/chriseth/go-ethereum/commit/3f3a599f08bea0843d4080eff64c4328ee819ff0) - but from the output it does not look like this is the culprit. Also I could sync goerli with this commit on top.\r\nAlso unfortunately I do not have the full error output - unfortunately the tmux buffer was too small (I increased it now - so if it happens again I might have a better log)\r\nAnyway I think better reporting once too often than having such a problem in some critical setup - but feel free to close if this issue is not actionable. \r\nHere the output:\r\n[geth_crash.txt](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/files/4390895/geth_crash.txt)\r\n",
